            <div class='post' itemprop='text'>
              <h3>Bot as an external tool</h3>
<p>In general I think the only downside, like you said, is this limits the integration possibility with the Redash UI, which I think is the ideal workflow here. That being said, it‚Äôd probably be okay for users to have to grab a link and type something like <code>/redash &lt;url to visualization&gt; &lt;time of day&gt;</code>  into a Slack channel.</p>
<h3>Schedule consistency</h3>
<p>The other issue is scheduling consistency between queries and slack posts. The more I think about this, the more I‚Äôm leaning in support of having them separate. The UX seems to get much more complicated when we talk about having them on the same schedule. The downside there might be possible confusion for users (ie. ‚ÄúDid it post this chart after the query ran or before? How do I make sure it only happens after?‚Äù). I don‚Äôt think that would be an issue with how <em>we</em> use scheduled queries, but I can‚Äôt speak for all users.</p>
            </div>

            <div itemprop="interactionStatistic" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/InteractionCounter">
